.TH "ocs_hcu_hw_cfg" 9 "ocs_hcu_hw_cfg" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
ocs_hcu_hw_cfg \- Configure the HCU hardware.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" ocs_hcu_hw_cfg
.BI "(struct ocs_hcu_dev *hcu_dev "  ","
.BI "enum ocs_hcu_algo algo "  ","
.BI "bool use_hmac "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hcu_dev" 12
The HCU device to configure.
.IP "algo" 12
The algorithm to be used by the HCU device.
.IP "use_hmac" 12
Whether or not HW HMAC should be used.
.SH "RETURN"
0 on success, negative error code otherwise.
